##Speakers

Our schedule has not been determined yet. We are seeking 8 speakers for 45 minute talks and 5 lightning talks
during lunch. 

Submit your papers here: <a href="https://www.papercall.io/indypy-conf" target="_blank">
https://www.papercall.io/indypy-conf</a>

The CFP ends Feb. 8th at 12am EST. 

Here are a few suggested categories/topics:
- For Business:
  - Taking Excel to the Next Level with Python
- How to stay relevant for Sysadmins
  - Python for Sysadmin (shell scripts > Python > services)
  - Configuration Management/Orchestration using Salt
  - Scheduled Job and Ad Hoc Task Management with Salt
  - Python and Lambda for Serverless
- For Developers:
  - Continuous Integration
  - Packaging: Docker
  - Using the `requests` Library for Accessing APIs
  - Deployment Automation
- IoT
  - Data Management in IoT
  - Machine Learning and Forecasting
  - IOT Device Management and Deployment
